  "text": "The Cephx authentication protocol in Ceph spans two main directories. In src/auth/cephx/: CephxServiceHandler (server-side auth handling), CephxClientHandler (client-side auth), CephxProtocol.h (defines protocol message types CEPHX_GET_AUTH_SESSION_KEY, CEPHX_GET_PRINCIPAL_SESSION_KEY, CEPHX_GET_ROTATING_KEY plus CephXAuthorizer struct), CephxKeyServer (KeyServer class for key rotation and ticket generation), CephxAuthorizeHandler (authorize verification), CephxSessionHandler (session-level crypto). In src/auth/: Auth.h defines the AuthAuthorizer interface, AuthAuthorizerChallenge, RotatingSecrets, and ExpiringCryptoKey. AuthServiceHandler/AuthClientHandler are abstract bases with factory create() methods that instantiate Cephx handlers. RotatingKeyRing manages rotating keys. AuthRegistry routes auth methods. In src/mon/: MonClient contains the authentication handshake (authenticate(), handle_auth(), _check_auth_rotating(), build_authorizer()). AuthMonitor is the Paxos service managing auth state on monitors. Monitor.h/cc ties it together.",
